headline: 1 Healthcare Stock to Research Further and 2 That Underwhelm
summary: Healthcare companies are pushing the status quo by innovating in areas like drug development and digital health. Shareholders who bet on the industry have been rewarded lately as healthcare stocks have returned 14.6% over the past six months, topping the S&P 500 by 1.5 percentage points.

headline: Molina Healthcare (MOH): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q3 Earnings?
summary: What a brutal six months it’s been for Molina Healthcare. The stock has dropped 42.1% and now trades at $168.08, rattling many shareholders. This was partly due to its softer quarterly results and might have investors contemplating their next move.
